  "translations": {
    "en": "As for the right of your slave, know he is your Lord's creature, the son of your father and mother, your flesh and blood. You did not make him; Allah made him. You created none of his limbs nor provide his sustenance, but Allah sufficed that, then subjected him to you and entrusted him to you. So treat him well as Allah treated you well. If you dislike him, replace him, but do not torment Allah's creature. There is no strength save in Allah.",
